,"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Open the `.dmg` and drag **Mate** into your Applications folder"},"404":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-29","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Launch Mate from Applications — if macOS shows a security warning, go to **System Settings > Privacy & Security** and click **Open Anyway**"},"405":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-30","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Mate bundles its own Node.js runtime, so you do not need Node installed separately"},"406":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-31","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Download the `.zip` file from the releases page"},"407":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-32","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Extract the zip to a folder of your choice (e.g. `C:\\Program Files\\Mate`)"},"408":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-33","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Run `Mate.exe` to launch"},"409":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-34","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Node.js is bundled — no separate installation needed"},"410":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-35","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Download the `.tar.gz` file from the releases page"},"411":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-36","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Extract it: `tar xzf mate-linux-*.tar.gz`"},"412":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-37","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Run the `mate` binary from the extracted folder"},"413":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-38","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Node.js is bundled with the app"},"414":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-39","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#mobile-apps","content":"iOS and Android apps are available for pairing with a desktop running Mate. Mobile devices act as remote mirrors — they connect to your desktop over the local network and let you interact with your sessions from your phone or tablet."},"415":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-40","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#mobile-apps","content":"Mobile devices do not run terminals or AI agents locally. They connect to a paired desktop that does the heavy lifting. See Pairing Devices for setup instructions."},"416":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-41","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#verify-the-installation","content":"After launching Mate, you should see the workspace with a default terminal tab. Try typing a command to confirm everything works:"},"417":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-42","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#verify-the-installation","content":"If the terminal responds, you are good to go. Head to First Session to learn the basics."},"418":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"page","content":"Pairing Devices","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices"},"419":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-0","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Pair your phone or another computer with Mate over your local network."},"420":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-1","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"How pairing works"},"421":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-2","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Launch Mate on both devices"},"422":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-3","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Wait for discovery"},"423":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-4","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Tap to pair"},"424":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-5","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"What paired devices can do"},"425":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-6","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Network requirements"},"426":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-7","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Troubleshooting pairing"},"427":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-8","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#multiple-devices","content":"Multiple devices"},"428":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-9","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Mate lets you access your desktop sessions from any device on the same network. Your desktop is the server — it runs the terminals, AI agents, and editors. Paired devices are live mirrors that connect directly, with no cloud involved."},"429":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-10","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"Mate uses multicast UDP for automatic device discovery on your local network. When two devices running Mate are on the same Wi-Fi or LAN, they find each other automatically. No manual IP entry, no account creation, no cloud relay."},"430":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-11","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Open Mate on your desktop and on the device you want to pair (phone, tablet, or another computer)."},"431":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-12","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Devices on the same network appear automatically in the sidebar within a few seconds. You will see the other device's name show up under the device list."},"432":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-13","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Select the discovered device in the sidebar. The first connection establishes the pairing. Once paired, the device remembers the connection for future sessions."},"433":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-14","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Once paired, the remote device can:"},"434":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-15","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"View and interact with all terminal sessions running on the desktop"},"435":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-16","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Chat with AI agents that are running on the desktop"},"436":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-17","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Browse and edit files through the IDE"},"437":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-18","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Preview web apps running on the desktop's localhost"},"438":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-19","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Send and receive files"},"439":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-20","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Mobile devices (iOS/Android) do not run sessions locally. All terminals, agent chats, and IDE sessions live on the desktop. The mobile app is a remote viewer and controller."},"440":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-21","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Both devices must be on the **same local network** (same Wi-Fi or LAN)"},"441":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-22","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Mate uses TCP port **53317** by default for communication (configurable in Settings)"},"442":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-23","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Multicast UDP must not be blocked by your router — most home and office networks allow it"},"443":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-24","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"No internet connection is required for pairing"},"444":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-25","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"If devices don't discover each other:"},"445":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-26","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Confirm both devices are on the same Wi-Fi network"},"446":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-27","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Check that no firewall is blocking port 53317 (TCP) or multicast (UDP)"},"447":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-28","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"On macOS, ensure Mate has local network permission in **System Settings > Privacy & Security > Local Network**"},"448":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-29","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Try restarting Mate on both devices — this triggers a fresh multicast scan"},"449":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-30","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"If automatic discovery fails, check Remote Troubleshooting for manual connection options"},"450":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-31","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#multiple-devices","content":"You can pair multiple devices with the same desktop. Each paired device appears in the sidebar, and switching between them shows that device's remote sessions. Your local device is always listed first."},"451":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"page","content":"Claude Code Integration","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Integrations"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code"},"452":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-0","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","content":"How Claude Code CLI works inside Mate's agent chat."},"453":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-1","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"How it works"},"454":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-2","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#requirements","content":"Requirements"},"455":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-3","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#features-in-mate","content":"Features in Mate"},"456":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-4","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#streaming-responses","content":"Streaming responses"},"457":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-5","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"Tool use visualization"},"458":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-6","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#conversation-persistence","content":"Conversation persistence"},"459":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-7","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#conversation-forking","content":"Conversation forking"},"460":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-8","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#mcp-connector-passthrough","content":"MCP connector passthrough"},"461":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-9","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-approval","content":"Tool approval"},"462":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-10","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#remote-usage","content":"Remote usage"},"463":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-11","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tips","content":"Tips"},"464":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-12","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","content":"Claude Code is the most deeply integrated AI CLI in Mate. Unlike Codex and Copilot (which run one-shot), Claude Code maintains a persistent process with multi-turn conversation support, making it feel like a native part of the app."},"465":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-13","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"When you start an agent chat with Claude Code:"},"466":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-14","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"Mate spawns the `claude` CLI with `--input-format stream-json` for streaming communication"},"467":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-15","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"The process stays alive for the entire conversation — follow-up messages go through stdin"},"468":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-16","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"Responses stream back in real time with text, tool calls, and results"},"469":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-17","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"MCP connectors are passed via a generated config file"},"470":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-18","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"This long-lived process model means there is no multi-second delay between messages. After the initial startup, follow-ups are instant."},"471":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-19","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#requirements","content":"You need the Claude Code CLI installed on your system:"},"472":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-20","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#requirements","content":"Mate detects available CLIs automatically. If `claude` is in your PATH, it appears as an option when creating an agent chat."},"473":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-21","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#streaming-responses","content":"Text and tool use stream in real time. You see the agent's thinking as it happens, not just the final result."},"474":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-22","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"When Claude Code calls tools, Mate shows them as interactive chips with context:"},"475":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-23","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"**File reads** show the filename"},"476":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-24","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"**Shell commands** show the actual command being run"},"477":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-25","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"**Searches** show the query"},"478":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-26","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"**File edits** show the file being modified, with inline diffs"},"479":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-27","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#conversation-persistence","content":"Conversations persist across app restarts. You can close Mate, reopen it, and resume where you left off."},"480":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-28","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#conversation-forking","content":"Fork a conversation at any point to explore a different approach without losing the original thread. This is useful for trying alternative solutions."},"481":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-29","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#mcp-connector-passthrough","content":"All enabled MCP connectors are automatically available to Claude Code. Mate generates an MCP config file that the CLI reads at startup, giving the agent access to GitHub, databases, search engines, and every other connector you have configured."},"482":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-30","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#mcp-connector-passthrough","content":"Mate handles the MCP config file generation automatically. You do not need to manually configure Claude Code's MCP settings — just enable connectors in Mate's settings and they are available in every agent chat."},"483":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-31","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-approval","content":"Some tool calls require your approval before execution. Mat